ent of independent inspections of garment factories the plan called for inspectors to have the power to close unsafe factories the proposal entailed a legally binding contract between suppliers customers and unions at a meeting in  in dhaka major european and north american retailers including gap rejected the proposal further efforts by unions to advance the proposal after numerous and deadly factory fires have been rejected after the  savar building collapse kohls became a founding member of the alliance for bangladesh worker safety on february   glenn murphy ceo of gap inc announced gap will raise the minimum wages for its  us store employees managementedit leadershipedit the current leadership is art peck chief executive officer teri liststoll evp and cfo jeff kirwan president  ceo gap mark breitbard president  ceo banana republic sonia syngal president  ceo old navy nancy green president and ceo athleta jyothi rao president and general manager intermix abinta malik evp and general manager greater china julie gruber evp general counsel corporate secretary chief compliance officer gap inc bobbi silten evp global talent  responsibility gap inc sebastian digrande evp strategy  chief customer officer gap inc paul chapman evp and chief information officer gap inc michael yee evp global supply chain sourcing and production gap inc shawn curran evp global supply chain logistics and product operations gap inc board of directorsedit domenico de sole doris f fisher  robert j fisher  chairman  chairman  william s fisher tracy gardner effective november   bella goren bob l martin jorge p montoya art peck mayo a shattuck iii katherine tsang padmasree warrior storesedit a branch on briggate in leeds west yorkshire as of the end of q  gap inc had  companyoperated or franchised stores in operation across  countries and had the ability to ship to  countries stores in brazil canada china france italy ireland japan uk and us including puerto rico are companyowned those outside of 