ch includingexpansion in asia the growing apparel markets in the east have attracted the retailer which is set to open  stores in india and  in china over the next year rising incomes and massive populations in the region make it an area of enormous potential for gap and its related lifestyle brandsacquisition of new brands shoppers have been familiar with gap brands banana republic and old navy for years but the company has continued to acquire new online and virtual brands such as piperlime athleta and intermix this has diversified its offerings as well as its target audiencesfewer brick and mortars in  gap closed the doors to  of its stores in the united states at the time the retailer cited higher efficiency and profit margins as the objective for its store closingsonline sales focus at the same time gap has been placing a greater emphasis on sales through gapcom which also conveniently links to its other brands for a seamless and allencompassing shopping experience for its brand enthusiasts although these tactics have met with varying levels of success their impact on the brands longterm growth and global reputation will continue to unfold over the next several years this will certainly serve as a lesson to its competitors as they formulate their global strategies both virtually and online how balancing physical  virtual locations helps companies when companies like gap operate brick and mortar retail establishments in addition to ecommerce websites the balancing act between the two can be a challenge however when businesses achieve this it yields a number of benefits to the corporation and its customers alike includingpersonal connections the ability to walk into a store try on clothes and talk with retail associates is something many shoppers value when too few physical stores remain within an individuals area he or she may choose companies with a stronger brick and mortar presencetouch points brands that meet their customers wherever they are stand the best chance of remaining competitive in a multidimensional economy those unlikely to visit a mall or shopping center may be more apt to make a purchase from an online retailer while online advertising and sales efforts may be lost on those preferring a more traditional shopping experiencepurchasing options online and instore shopping each present their own advantages and disadvantages which may apply to the same shoppers at different times during the same day month or week someone who needs a new outfit the next day cant afford to wait for a purchase to ship whereas someone with a busy work schedule may be unable to walk into a store during its business hours in addition an online purchase remains impossible for those seeking to pay with cashwhen providing online and instore shopping options one of the most important components of the retail experience is the point of sale a business offering a wide range of payment options and making the process as quick and uncomplicated as possible will enjoy the highest numbers of converted and returning customersone way to achieve this is by utilizing highquality pointofsale systems businesses of all sizes can accept a wide range of payment types with new mobile payment options such as square and paypal which attach directly to ones mobile device and allow them to complete transactions anywhere they travel for online businesses comprehensive pos systems such as shopify make completing purchases an attractive prospect for customersfor gap and other retailers combining brick and mortar and ecommerce locations it is crucial to make every aspect of the customers experience more convenient enjoyable and memorable with a balanced versatile and streamlined approach to business brands of all sizes can achieve sustained growth in their chosen marketsdo you think gap incs recent business strategies will ultimately help or harm the brand the opinions expressed here by inccom columnists are their own not those of inccom published on sep   global gap  projects abroad feedback you seem interested in our projects care to tell us more id be happy to not right now thanks menu search go volunteer overseas ­    infoprojectsabroadorg follow projabroadus search free brochure contact us live chat projects abroad projects global gap global gap year overview share tweet share email print  ghana  south africa  nepal  thailand  peru global gap is an innovative week volunteer program for gap year students who want a farranging international experience that spans three continents five countries and twelve different service opportunities by offering immersion opportunities in local communities around the globe global gap offers a unique way to explore new places learn about important global issues and help out on worthwhile volunteer projects the global gap program is designed for high school graduates taking a year off before university the program consists of a four week orientation and care program in ghana followed by onetotwo month programs in each of south africa peru nepal and thailand in each of these countries volunteers will work closely with our local staff members on projects that lend insight into important issues in developing countries like housing education environmental conservation and human rights the global gap program is tailored for a maximum of  volunteers and minimum of  the agenda is  september   september    week september   september    week orientation in accra ghana october   october    weeks september   october    weeks care in akuapem hills ghana  october   november    weeks october   november    weeks building in cape town south africa november   december    weeks november   december    weeks choice of project in cape town south africa december   – january    weeks december   – january    weeks winter break  january   march    weeks january   march    weeks teaching in cusco peru  march   april    weeks march   april    weeks choice of project in kathmandu nepal  april   may    weeks april   may    weeks diving  marine conservation in ao nang thailand see  dates the global gap allinclusive program fee is  this price includes all food and housing medical and travel insurance airport pick up and drop off in each destination as well as hour support from our staff unlike other projects abroad programs this program fee includes all required plane tickets from the us and canada including roundtrip tickets home for winter break this program fee also includes various sightseeing tours and activities in each destination volunteer profile kayla lehne  countries  incredible people and  unforgettable months i cant believe this year has come to a close ive learned more about myself and the greater world in the last eight months than i would have ever imagined and i wanted to thank everyone who has given me so much love and support personally and financially along the way because i wouldnt be in this place without you and for the memories and lessons that i have learned i cannot express my gratitude read more choose a global gap year stage ghana stage  orientation and care work all global gap participants meet in accra ghana for a one week orientation then they spend an additional three weeks in akuapem hills north of accra working on a care placement south africa stage  building  choice of project twice the size of texas south africas position at the southern tip of africa has created a diversity of lifestyles and environments at the start of the st century south africa is leading the way in african politics and is seen as an inspiration to other countries with eleven national languages and a variety of religions south africa truly is the rainbow nation peru stage  education peru is a fascinating and beautiful country with an extensive pacific coastline a vast area of amazon rainforest and the magnificent andes peru provides an opportunity for volunteers to experience much of what south america offers within just one country nepal stage  choice of project nepal is a small yet stunning land of snowcapped mountains majestic buddhist temples and the ancient capital city of kathmandu although nepal is known for the himalayas and mount everest it is actually one of the most biodiverse countries on the planet thailand stage conservation thailand is a great introduction to south east asia its a beautiful country with pristine beaches exotic food and golden temples however anyone doing international volunteer work in thailand will go beyond the country that tourists see and discover an incredibly friendly people with a unique culture webinars throughout the year projects abroad offers free webinars or virtual open houses presented by the us and canadian offices see when the next global gap webinar is scheduled you can also view a previously recorded global gap webinar media coverage projects abroad vice president tom pastorius speaks about the global gap program on nbc nightly news contact us chat online with a program advisor apply now contact us contact us submit chat online with a program advisor get a free brochure subscribe to our newsletter apply now as seen in media tell your friends about this page share google  tweet email back to top ▲ volunteer projects  projects abroad feedback you seem interested in our projects care to tell us more id be happy to not right now thanks menu search go volunteer overseas ­    infoprojectsabroadorg follow projabroadus search free brochure contact us live chat projects abroad projects volunteer abroad and intern abroad programs share tweet share email print we work in a wide range of projects located all around the world when you go abroad with projects abroad you specify when you want to go where and what project you want to do everywhere our volunteers go we employ fulltime professional staff to help you be effective in your job and generally to make sure that things go smoothly which project is best for me   age range anyone  anyone  teens  university age gap year professionals anyone  anyone  duration flexible flexible  weeks  week  months flexible  weeks  weeks start dates flexible flexible fixed  summer winter spring fixed  spring fixed  fall flexible fixed  spring and fall fixed  winter staff support weekly weekly constant daily weekly weekly daily daily volunteer  intern abroad projects for all ages international service projects for all ages anyone    our standard volunteer abroad projects are for anyone  and older to undertake valuable service work to benefit the communities in which we work almost all of our standard projects do not have any requirements and are suitable for anyone who wants to give back by volunteering abroad available throughout the year you can start anytime and choose your duration learn more care care volunteers work in orphanages care centers kindergartens and special needs clinics around the world you will help children get ready in the morning play games assist with homework and mealtimes etc these are very wellrounded volunteer placements that allow you to bring your own interests and passions in to share with the children teaching teaching volunteers work alongside local teachers in any of the destinations where we work you do not need to have previous experience just energy enthusiasm and patience you can teach english to students or adults and if you have the necessary skills you could also volunteer to teach french it music or sports conservation  environment conservation and environment projects focus on preserving some of the most beautiful and vulnerable ecosystems around the world whether you are volunteering in a rainforest on the coast or in a nature reserve you will be working alongside our dedicated local staff to protect the area and raise awareness about the importance of conservation sports sports volunteer programs are popular with those who have a background in playing or coaching soccer basketball volleyball water sports and more sports bring people together and help build strong communities as well as contribute to the creation of healthy happy individuals archaeology archaeology placements allow volunteers to explore an exciting new culture through history you can also gain valuable firsthand experience in the field of international archaeology these placements do not require any previous experience or field work take a step back in time while working on roman ruins in romania or walk the trails of the inca empire in peru building building volunteer placements involve some of the most important work needed in developing communities including setting up basic infrastructure volunteering to building schools libraries and homes lays a foundation that supports locals even after your volunteer work abroad has ended farming farming volunteers get their hands dirty helping schools and communities raise crops to support themselves farming volunteers also have an important role to play promoting responsible and sustainable farming practices in the communities in which they are working creative  performing arts creative  performing arts placements are great for those who have a background in music dance or drama and a passion for sharing their skills with another community volunteers impart their knowledge about their art form while learning the local traditions in their destination country view options gain professional experience abroad in a worthwhile field anyone    our standard intern abroad projects are for anyone  or older to develop skills in a particular field volunteers work alongside local professionals in the role of an intern and help as needed while the majority of standard projects do not have experience requirements you should have a strong interest in the field in which you are working available throughout the year you can start anytime and choose your duration learn more medicine  healthcare medicine  healthcare interns learn alongside doctors and other healthcare professionals in local hospitals or clinics in a developing country you can choose to focus on a number of different areas including medicine nursing midwifery dentistry public health physical therapy occupational therapy speech therapy and nutrition medical school electives choose to do your elective placement overseas medical dentistry nursing midwifery physical therapy and occupational therapy electives are available placements are tailored to meet your needs law  human rights interning abroad on a law and human rights placement provides interns with the opportunity to gain more indepth knowledge of the human rights abuses that occur around the world take an active role on campaigns and legislation to raise awareness and work closely with community leaders and human rights lawyers to eliminate these abuses journalism international interns on a journalism program learn directly from experienced journalists how to further their own writing and reporting skills volunteers who intern abroad on a journalism project work at a range of print and broadcast placements including newspapers magazines as well as radio and tv stations microfinance these projects aim to assist local entrepreneurs in starting their own businesses and building sustainable futures for themselves and their communities international development international development interns work at development organizations and public offices abroad interns can become directly involved in communitybased efforts to provide career opportunities to vulnerable populations back small loan projects and further disaster management planning business those interested in business gain experience in various fields including accounting marketing human resources public relations and more interns gain skills knowledge and experience essential to their future career veterinary medicine  animal care by interning abroad on a veterinary medicine  animal care placement volunteers further their interests or studies in the animal care field interns gain knowledge about veterinary care and the treatment of local animal populations internships for social work students intern abroad in the field of social work and gain practical experience and skills that you can use toward your degree you will work alongside professionals in care facilities and schools view options just for teens group service trips for high school students teens    high schools specials are for teens  years old to join a group of their peers participating in worthwhile service and professional development projects under the constant supervision of projects abroad staff these projects have set dates for week and week periods and follow a busy daily schedule including guided tourism trips and cultural activities learn more learn more just for gap years gap year program in  countries for  months gap year    global gap is for students taking a gap year between high school and college and want to spend the year traveling around the world doing volunteer work the program is designed for  students to go to  countries and participate in a wide variety of service and internship projects together global gap starts in the fall and runs for  months including returning home for a winter break learn more learn more just for university students alternative spring break volunteer trips for university students university age    the alternative spring break trips are short programs for college students to volunteer abroad together over spring break these projects are scheduled for week periods in february and march in some of our closest destinations learn more jamaica building as a volunteer in jamaica you will work alongside an experienced local builder and help replace dangerous pit latrines with safer and cleaner modern toilets in schools no construction experience is required sunday march th   saturday march th  belize care help provide care and educational support to underprivileged children in care centers and kindergartens in belize these placements have limited resources and local staff welcome an extra pair of helping hands sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th  costa rica care work at a local care center for children in the town of heredia near san jose you will have plenty of opportunity to plan activities for the kids so creativity is encouraged this project is great if you want to learn spanish or improve the skills you have sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th  fiji care help support children at a kindergarten in fiji by teaching basic literacy and numeracy games and songs as well as doing activities like arts  crafts sunday march th   saturday march th  jamaica care be a positive role model and lend a hand at an orphanage or care center in jamaica assisting the staff care for the children and providing fun and educational activities for the kids sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th  mexico conservation live at a camp on the pacific coast of mexico near a small village called tecoman in the state of colima volunteers protect endangered olive ridley turtles and their nests from predators development and poachers sunday february th   saturday february th sunday february th   saturday march rd sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th  argentina medicine gain valuable medical experience by interning at a hospital in cordoba where you will shadow local doctors and participate in workshops and outreaches sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th  ghana public health volunteer in cape coast ghana helping with public health campaigns including community health checks giving educational talks about health concerns and dressing wounds at schools orphanages and leprosy communities sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th  mexico public health volunteer in guadalajara mexico and get involved in immunization drives conducting basic health checks and leading educational campaigns about health and hygiene in schools orphanages community groups and slums sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th  belize public health use your spring break to gain meaningful experience in belize and give back to communities through health campaigns and outreach work sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th  ghana care provide ghanaian children with the support they need as a volunteer at an orphanage or school your focus will be on care education and doing maintenance and renovation work sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th  mexico international development gain meaningful experience working alongside an ngo in guadalajara during spring break you will work with various ngos such as amnesty international sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th sunday march th   saturday march th  view options just for professionals volunteering abroad for skilled professionals professionals    these projects are structured the same as our volunteer abroad and intern abroad programs but where volunteers work in roles where there is a specific need for people with professional experience start dates and duration of these projects are flexible to fit your schedule learn more archaeology work alongside fellow professionals to build upon your knowledge and skills while contributing to ongoing work at archaeological sites and helping to make new discoveries business as a professional business volunteer you may take on the role of a consultant or business advisor working with an ngo microfinance project or local entrepreneurs care depending on your background and experience you could join us as a social worker psychologist or art therapist in several of our destinations around the world journalism volunteers with professional qualifications in journalism or film production can pass on their skills on one of our journalism options overseas law  human rights as a qualified lawyer or human rights specialist you can help on a range of law and human rights related projects in africa or asia sharing your knowledge will assist the local staff medicine  healthcare qualified medical professionals can work in a range of areas depending on your specialism including working as a doctor nurse physiotherapist speech therapist or nutritionist teaching professional teachers are welcomed by many of our destinations around the world to teach subjects such as english math science pe and special needs classes veterinary medicine qualified vets can help in clinics and assist with training staff and volunteers in the south pacific or latin america your skills and experience will be welcomed by the local staff view options just for  group service trips for volunteers over   grownup specials are for anyone  or older to join volunteers of their own age on organized service trips in developing countries across the world these projects do not have any requirements and each project has set dates for week periods learn more learn more special arrangements explore new cultures and extraordinary lifestyles anyone    culture  community projects offer volunteers the chance to be closely involved with unique communities abroad in most cases you will be fully immersed in their daily lives living and working alongside them and learning about their culture flexible start dates and durations learn more cambodia  khmer project khmer project explore the ancient civilizations and engaging culture of modern cambodia on our khmer project learn some of the khmer language cooking and local crafts and visit the main sites of phnom penh and the magnificent temples at angkor wat fiji  community village project community village project fully immerse yourself into the exciting culture of this beautiful island nation by living and violunteering in a traditional fijian village you will live with a fijian host family and help with the daytoday task of the village including teaching farming cooking basket weaving mat making and gardening jamaica  maroon community project maroon community project live with a traditional maroon community in jamaica the jamaican maroons were runaway slaves who fought the british during the th century working alongside members of the maroon community will help with a wide variety of tasks from teaching reading to cultural preservation projects mongolia  nomad project nomad project live and work on the mongolian steppe with a nomadic family riding horses and camels and collecting firewood are all part of daily life in the desert morocco  nomad project nomad project join a moroccan nomadic family living in the largest desert on the planet  the sahara you will get to help with the livestock prepare meals and retrieve water while learning about the nomadic culture and way of life south africa  community township project community township project help build a community center in the township of lavender hill and contribute to various community projects including nutrition and childcare tanzania  community village project community village project experience a unique insight into the maasai tribes way of life and play a vital role when it comes to helping the maasai people view options winter break group trips for volunteers of all ages anyone    our winter break trips are shortterm volunteer programs for anyone ages  and older these trips take place during the winter break on fixed dates in december and january volunteers can choose from week and week trips learn more ghana care  community volunteer in ghana and help make a difference in the lives of children in an orphanage or day care center you will also contribute to valuable renovation activities in the community wednesday december th   tuesday january nd  